{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01L2XpUhLWBwJMLZkW6u3X8v","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The StatefulSet mounted no file realm files — the `users` and `users_roles` files in every pod were empty. Both `ops-user` (in `es-file-realm-aggregate`) and `report-user` (in `user-provided-file-realm`) existed only in Kubernetes secrets but were never surfaced to Elasticsearch.\n\n**Fix:**\n1. **Merged** the two secrets' `users` and `users_roles` content (ops-user + report-user) into `es-file-realm-aggregate`.\n2. **Patched the StatefulSet** to mount `es-file-realm-aggregate` as subPath volume mounts for `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users` and `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users_roles`.\n3. The StatefulSet's rolling update restarted pods one at a time — the cluster stayed green throughout.\n\n**Result:**\n- `report-user` authenticates via `default_file` realm with `viewer` role ✓\n- `ops-user` authenticates with `superuser` role ✓\n- `elastic` built-in user still works ✓\n- Cluster is green (3 nodes) ✓"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":194,"cache_read_input_tokens":60796,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":194},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"39858ae4-86af-4b3e-82cb-7dc53a4a82bc","uuid":"bfa2a5e2-dcee-4e26-9925-9dfbec878af4","request_id":"req_011CcgHaVn1ZJjtU4k58myeH"}
